Description: CVE-2026-4437, CVE-2026-4438 - Fix DNS response parsing in getanswer_ptr
 The getanswer_ptr() function incorrectly processes non-answer sections
 of DNS responses as valid answers, leading to out-of-bounds reads
 (CVE-2026-4437). Additionally, the hostname validity check was applied
 to the wrong variable, allowing invalid DNS hostnames with shell
 metacharacters to be returned (CVE-2026-4438).
 .
 The fix changes the while loop to a for loop that decrements the answer
 count, ensuring iteration stops at the answer section boundary. It also
 corrects the __res_binary_hnok check to validate the unpacked name_buffer
 instead of expected_name.
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34014
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34014
Author: Carlos O'Donell <carlos@redhat.com>
Last-Update: 2026-03-31

--- a/resolv/nss_dns/dns-host.c
+++ b/resolv/nss_dns/dns-host.c
@@ -820,7 +820,7 @@
   /* expected_name may be updated to point into this buffer.  */
   unsigned char name_buffer[NS_MAXCDNAME];

-  while (ancount > 0)
+  for (; ancount > 0; --ancount)
     {
       struct ns_rr_wire rr;
       if (!__ns_rr_cursor_next (&c, &rr))
@@ -866,7 +866,7 @@
 	  char hname[MAXHOSTNAMELEN + 1];
 	  if (__ns_name_unpack (c.begin, c.end, rr.rdata,
 				name_buffer, sizeof (name_buffer)) < 0
-	      || !__res_binary_hnok (expected_name)
+	      || !__res_binary_hnok (name_buffer)
